New $107 Million Najran Airport Operating Smoothly, Saudis Say

-- B y   S a r a h   A b d u l l a h
-- 
2011-09-22T17:57:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/new-107-million-najran-airport-operating-smoothly-saudis-say.html
The new Najran Regional Airport,
690 kilometers (429 miles) southeast of  Jeddah , is operational,
 Saudi Arabia ’s General Authority of Civil Aviation said.  The $107 million airport received its first flight on Sept.
20, arriving from King Abdul Aziz Airport in Jeddah, according
to an e-mailed statement today.  “The passengers all exited the airport smoothly,
indicating the success of the new operational plan,” GACA said
in the same statement.  The Najran airport is the latest in a series of regional
and international airport projects currently being constructed
in the kingdom.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sarah Abdullah in Johannesburg at 
